      "content": "# always check document model schema before calling addActions\n\nBefore dispatching any actions via `addActions`, always call `getDocumentModelSchema` to understand the input requirements:\n\n```\nmcp__reactor-mcp__getDocumentModelSchema({ type: \"powerhouse/document-model\" })\n```\n\nThis reveals required fields (like `id` or `scope`), valid enum values, and input shapes. Without this step, actions frequently fail due to missing or malformed parameters.\n\nThis applies to all document types — document models, editors, apps, and drives. Since [[document model changes require both MCP update and src file update]], understanding the schema prevents wasted round trips on both sides.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[mcp workflows]]",
